    "summary": "Steffen Pauws, \n\nI am a distinguished Principal Scientist in Data & AI, an inspirational Team Lead, a proud Professor in 'Risk Modelling and Communication in Healthcare', and a seasoned grant writer and coordinator. \n\nI act as a driving and pioneering force in Research & Innovation for Philips - Outpatient and Home - Healthcare business and markets.  With a team sized 10-15 Data & AI experts, I create AI models and algorithms for sleep, respiratory care, diabetes care and cardiology in outpatient or home healthcare settings. My own work has led to business transfers (20+) and propositions in the market. \n\nI work with clinical partners from renowned hospitals and clinics in the US, UK, Japan, India, Singapore, and the Netherlands. \n\nI have authored more than 100 scientific publications and hold close to 25 patents and more than 40 patent applications on Music Technology and Healthtech. I coordinated and/or co-wrote 15 EU and 9 national submitted grant proposals. \n\nI hold an Endowed Professorship with a Special Appointment on \u2018Risk Modelling and Risk Communication in Healthcare'.  Since November 2014, I have a Honorary Fellow position at Leiden University Medical Center for data science consultancy in Neonatal Intensive Care.\n\nPrior to joining Philips Research, I worked as PhD candidate, post-doc and Researcher in Language, Speech Music Technology at the Institute for Perception Research (IPO) of the Eindhoven University of Technology (TU/e). I hold a PhD from the Technical University of Eindhoven, since 2000, in Music Recommender Technology, a PDEng degree on Software Technology, and a Master of Science in Medical Informatics from Leiden University.\n\nExpertise on: | Healthcare Data Science | Artificial Intelligence in Healthcare | Health Risk Modelling | People management | Grant Writing and Coordination |",
